<plot>To understand someone you have to try and see things from their point of view. Seeing is believing in P.O.V. as you not only share each characters point of view, but also their thoughts. You will travel to the darkest recesses of the human and not so human mind. Experience one evening as six very different people with drastically differing perspectives pass the time discussing sex, violence and one very uptight friend.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?419405</url></doc>
